reviews.text:
It’s like peanut butter and strawberry jam on thick homemade wheat, minus the peanut butter. I totally dig it. That strawberry combo can run quite candied depending on what it’s mixed with, but something about the way it works with this combo tastes like jam. Maybe it’s the way the almond and honeycomb blend in there. The thing tastes amazing but speaking of, I’m not getting any discrete almond, just a nice nuttyness like good wheat bread has. Same with the Honeycomb, it doesn’t really taste like honey to me here or on it’s own, though it does seem to be bringing a very honey-ish sweetness, like honey wheat bread. I would love to know what’s keeping it from seeming too dry. It’s like a thick hunk of fresh bread with emphasis on the fresh, not some dried out grocery store bullshit. I think this is the most interesting juice I’ve encountered so far this year.&#xD;
&#xD;
You could leave this as it is because it’s already awesome, but I can see a lot of ways to play and experiment with it. Add some butter - strawberry jam on lightly toasted toast. Add some hops - strawberry wheat beer. Might as well put some PB in there and make a sandwich. Add some banana just because banana and strawberry. So many possibilities.
